  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Discord messages can contain actual uploaded image data:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n      \"attachments\": [\r\n        {\r\n          \"id\": \"1001494606019579956\",\r\n          \"url\": \"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1001494102640173066/1001494606019579956/Screenshot_from_2022-05-29_13-37-24.png\",\r\n          \"fileName\": \"Screenshot_from_2022-05-29_13-37-24.png\",\r\n          \"fileSizeBytes\": 2127583\r\n        }\r\n      ],\r\n```\r\nSuch messages need to be translated to status image messages.\r\nTo make this work, we'll have to download the asset during import and set the `ChatMessage` content payload to image type.\r\n\r\nAnother thing we could do is keep the image URL in the text payload, so that if the image couldn't be successfully downloaded, status could fallback simply rendering the image from the URL\r\n",
