    "body": "Alright, a simple version of this is working.\r\n\r\nImage messages are being downloaded, base64 encoded and then attached to `common.Message.DiscordMessage` as `Attachments`.\r\n\r\nIn desktop this is handled rudimentary by check if there's any attachments on the discord message, if yes, the first attachment will be considered an image (this will change so we can check more explicitly what attachments we're dealing with)",
